<!--Article 1-->
    <article id="S09062015">
      <h2>Sound &#38 Color – Alabama Shakes</h2><br />
      <h3>Album Spotlight:</h3><br />
      <p>Released in April, 2015 Alabama Shakes’ second album was released just over three years after their debut album <i>Boys &#38 Girls</i> features top singles such as <i>Gimme All Your Love </i> and <i> Don’t Wanna Fight:</i></p>
    <div class="youtube">
      <iframe width="640" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/x-5OX7CO26c" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </div>
      <p>The album was appreciated around the globe reaching number 1 in the US Billboard 200 and number 6 in the UK album charts. Sound &#38 Color demonstrates Alabama Shakes truly unique and mesmerising style that endears the listener to never stop listening, it has also fascinated the critics who have described the album as a: <blockquote>deliberately weird record, but authentically weird; it's chaotic yet cohesive, full of sound, colour and unshakable vision</blockquote> Which perfectly describes the beautiful sound that Alabama Shakes creates.</p>
      <br />
      <p class="date">09/06/2015</p>
    </article>

